description.plain:
John Paul Cooper, better known as JP Cooper, is an English singer-songwriter. He was born in 1983 in Middleton, England in a musical Catholic family.

He is most well-known for his feature on Jonas Blue’s track, “Perfect Strangers”, which got popular worldwide and went platinum in the UK.

He started off with releasing 3 self-released EP’s, then got signed to Island Records and released the two EP’s, Keep the Quiet Out and When the Darkness Comes.

Cooper released “September Song” in September 2016, which was his first song in top 10 in the UK. “September Song” went to be a part of Cooper’s first studio album, Raised Under Grey Skies.

songs.title: September Song

description.plain: “September Song” is about a young romance that the singer misses. Even though the relationship happened when he was 15, after all these years he remembers it as something beautiful and he misses her. He remembers her as his “September Song.”
